[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# Deploying the Model\n\nThis notebook shows how you can score data using models built in this lesson.\n\nThe training and test tables as well as the models' scoring materials have been built in previous steps.\n\nIn case you have not followed previous steps, you need, at least, to run the following SAS notebook:\n\n**sas-education/sas1/03_Addressing_the_Use_Case_with_the_SAS_Language/03_Machine_Learning/03_Developing_a_Model.sasnb**\n\nFrom the results of the 03_Developing_a_Model.sasnb SAS notebook, we decide that the Gradient Boosting model has the best fit statistics of all three models.\n\nSince the Gradient Boosting model is the champion model, we will register it in the Model Manager Repository.\n\n## Scoring Data in SAS Viya Workbench","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Proc logselect - built the model - created the score code\n\nThe score code was created in previous steps using this type of code:\n\n```sas \nproc logselect data=work.customer_churn_ml_train_final;\n    class &char_vars &target;\n    model &target(event='1')=&char_vars &num_vars;\n    /* Specify variable selection technique*/\n    selection method=elasticnet;\n    /* Generate score code */\n    code file=\"&path/code/logscore.sas\";\nrun;\n```","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Score a data set using the score code from the logistic regression model","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"title2 'Score data with a %include statement referencing SAS Data Step code from proc logselect';\ndata log_scored ;\n   set churn.customer_churn_ml_test_final;\n   %include \"&path/code/logscore.sas\";\nrun;","outputs":[{"items":[{"data":"[\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1754  /** LOG_START_INDICATOR **/\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1755  title;footnote;ods _all_ close;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1756  ods graphics on;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1757  ods html5(id=vscode) style=HTMLEncore options(bitmap_mode='inline' svg_mode='inline');\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"NOTE: Writing HTML5(VSCODE) Body file: sashtml79.htm\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1758  %let _SASPROGRAMFILE =\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1758! %nrquote(%nrstr(/workspaces/churnproject/sas-education/sas1/03_Addressing_the_Use_Case_with_the_SAS_Language/04_Productionizin\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1758! g_the_Model/01_Deploying_the_Model.sasnb));\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1759  title2 'Score data with a %include statement referencing SAS Data Step code from proc logselect';\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1760  data log_scored ;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1761     set churn.customer_churn_ml_test_final;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1762     %include \\\"&path/code/logscore.sas\\\";\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1918   run;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"NOTE: There were 1499 observations read from the data set CHURN.CUSTOMER_CHURN_ML_TEST_FINAL.\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"NOTE: The data set WORK.LOG_SCORED has 1499 observations and 32 variables.\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"NOTE: DATA statement used (Total process time):\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"      real time           0.00 seconds\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"      cpu time            0.01 seconds\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"      \",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1919   ;*';*\\\";*/;run;quit;ods html5(id=vscode) close;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1920   \",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t}\n]","mime":"application/vnd.sas.compute.log.lines"}]}]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"### Print a few observations with the scores","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"proc sort data=log_scored ;\n    by descending P_LostCustomer ;\nrun ;\nproc print data=log_scored (obs=10) ;\n    var ID customerGender customerSubscrStat DemHomeOwner I_LostCustomer P_LostCustomer ;\nrun ;","outputs":[{"items":[{"data":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\" xml:lang=\"en\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\"/>\n<meta content=\"SAS V.04.00\" name=\"generator\"/>\n<title>SAS Output</title>\n<style>\n/*<![CDATA[*/\n.body.c > table, .body.c > pre, .body.c div > table,\n.body.c div > pre, .body.c > table, .body.c > pre,\n.body.j > table, .body.j > pre, .body.j div > table,\n.body.j div > pre, .body.j > table, .body.j > pre,\n.body.c p.note, .body.c p.warning, .body.c p.error, .body.c p.fatal,\n.body.j p.note, .body.j p.warning, .body.j p.error, .body.j p.fatal,\n.body.c > table.layoutcontainer, .body.j > table.layoutcontainer { margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto }\n.layoutregion.l table, .layoutregion.l pre, .layoutregion.l p.note,\n.layoutregion.l p.warning, .layoutregion.l p.error, .layoutregion.l p.fatal { margin-left: 0 }\n.layoutregion.c table, .layoutregion.c pre, .layoutregion.c p.note,\n